34761	FFD700	‚òÖHalfway Galaxy	^ffd200The sorrow in you begins to burn, \rThe tears begin to bite. \rYou try to hide your fearful visage, \rWith your eyes clenched so tight.	1	0	1		2037
34762	FFD700	‚òÖInfinite Longing	^ffd200Gone are the days of yore, \rAll that's left... a mere memory, \rRegret festers like a sore.	1	0	1		2037
34763	FFD700	‚òÖAstral Ballad	^ffd200Our boatswain hums a somber shanty, \rA ballad of death and dying, \rIt fails to ease your restless worry, \rFails to quell your crying.	1	0	1		2037
34764	FFD700	‚òÖUnicorn's Tragedy	^ffd200'Fear not the river,' he says, \rHis gaze fixed on us, \r'It may bewilder, but take heed, we all enter and exit the same way.'	1	0	1		2037
34765	FFD700	‚òÖResonance of Pride	^ffd200We reach our destination, \rThe landscape soft and white, \rSo pure the snow we crunch underfoot, \rA deceptive, calming sight.	1	0	1		2037
34766	FFD700	‚òÖChill of Blizzard	^ffd200The delicate flurries flutter, float, falling forth from far above. \rOur footsteps they obfuscate, \rWe've nowhere to go but anywhere.	1	0	1		2037
34767	FFD700	‚òÖSpirit of Justice	^ffd200We gnaw away the miles, \rWith talk of memories past. \rThe brewing blizzard beguiles, \rNightmarish visions amass.	1	0	1		2037
34768	FFD700	‚òÖGalaxy Shocker	^ffd200We press onward, \rAnd pay the phantasms no mind. \rWe steel ourselves against their tricks, \rTrying to leave them behind.	1	0	1		2037
34769	FFD700	‚òÖWaves of Glacier	^ffd200The horrors jeer and taunt, \rWith crinkled hands they tear. \rTheir faces bleak and gaunt, \rSadistic grins they wear.	1	0	1		2037
34770	FFD700	‚òÖJaden Emperor's Defiance	^ffd200We run until we can no more, \rWe cross the desert's edge,\r Looking out across the dunes, \rI've now fulfilled my pledge.	1	0	1		2037
34771	FFD700	‚òÖStellar Vibration	^ffd200The sand does glisten, \rKissed by the nurturing sun. \rOn the warm rocks we sit and listen, \rNature's song's begun.	1	0	1		2037
34772	FFD700	‚òÖAncestor's Sorrow	^ffd200Softly it begins, \rWith a chirp from a bird, \rThen bursts into chorus, \rThe desert's residents stirred.	1	0	1		2037
34773	FFD700	‚òÖFoundation of World	^ffd200The symphony plays, \rThe stars come out. \rOn the warm rocks we lay, \rWhile around us, a forest sprouts.	1	0	1		2037
34774	FFD700	‚òÖSilence of Frost	^ffd200It is time for me to take my leave, I'm afraid \rI've already stayed too long. \rI have lost ones to shepherd, you see. \rThey need to hear this song.	1	0	1		2037
34775	FFD700	‚òÖSandy World	^ffd200I leave you here, just like the rest. \rConfusion crosses your face, \r'This is how it is,' I say, \rAnd vanish without a trace.	1	0	1		2037
34776	FFD700	‚òÖGlaive of Nirvana	^ffd200What happens now, you ask? \rBut only you know this. \rI am but a humble guide, \rAn escort into bliss.	1	0	1		2037
34777	FFD700	‚òÖTraceless Dimension	^ffd200Now you are truly free, my dear \rOf life's dues and catches. \rOf hunger, of pain, of sickness and war, \rOf bruises, of scrapes and scratches.	1	0	1		2037
34778	FFD700	‚òÖPeak of Clouds	^ffd200Rest your tired eyes now, \rFor you've all the time you need. \rTo ponder the universe's wonders, \rTo lay amongst the reeds.	1	0	1		2037
34779	FFD700	‚òÖNetherworld Guidance	^ffd200Dream a dream, of a life so new, \rOne brimming with potential, \rOf starting again, leaving all behind, \rOnly happiness is essential.	1	0	1		2037
34780	FFD700	‚òÖBuddha's Hatred	^ffd200You've arrived, at last! \r But your journey's just begun. \rExplore this existence, but remember: we are all one.	1	0	1		2037
