50075	8C8CEF	Sheomay Trophy	^FFCB4AA mystical woman with breathtaking beauty. It is said that she\rhas the most alluring voice and dancing postures. But,no one\rknows where she came from or how she ended up in Perfect World.\rNumerous people around the world seek her, hoping to lay their\reyes upon her beauty.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50076	8C8CEF	Sarokkan Trophy	^FFCB4AThis one is the high general of Tyrant Army. It's skilled, ruthless,\rand widely ambitious! This other-worldly creature\r would wander around the Dragon Pond on occasion.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50077	8C8CEF	Queen Liu Soo Trophy	^FFCB4AThis one is the Queen of Mirrorflower Kingdom, a 'no man's land'. The dwellers there\rrelied on the River of Birth to breed, until\ra man called Ren Dao showed up and took their beloved river. Since then, the queen has been looking for a pair of helping hands to retrieve what was theirs.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50078	8C8CEF	Tree Raccoon Chieftain Trophy	^FFCB4AThis one is the chief of Tree Raccoon Village. His fear of Tyrant has led\rhim to sign a false agreement with their enemies, and hence, the Bamboo Raccoon Village has started to distrust the man and his village. \r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50079	8C8CEF	Northern Star Trophy	^FFCB4AOne of the finest soldiers of the Primal World is Pathkeeper Bajan.  \rOnce a nameless warrior, he now guards the Trial of Unity in the Uncharted Paradise.\rHis unwavering courage and valor in the face of opposition make him a a fearsome opponent.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50080	8C8CEF	Leaf Rain Dryad Trophy	^FFCB4APeachblossom Ritualist's sister, who also lived in Lothranis.\rAfter Peachblossom Fairy became Peachblossom Ritualist, she\rfollowed her to Momaganon and abandoned her celestial form.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50081	8C8CEF	Skyscreamer Trophy	^FFCB4AThe wraiths in the Deserted Sea near the Hidden Dragon Den\rspent many years creating a powerful devil. Hiding deep in the\rHidden Dragon Den, the ferocious devil waits for people who are\rled there by the Fire Dragon Clan.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50082	8C8CEF	Damned Gaurnob Trophy	^FFCB4AThe Wraiths appointed two of their strongest guards\rto patrol the Wraithgate. Though Cenequus Polearm\rcommands the entire Dreadmarsh Legion, he is not\runwilling to impale intruders upon his spear.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50083	8C8CEF	Grand Wizard Tensa Trophy 	^FFCB4AGrand Wizard Tensa is the most powerful Human wizardof all time.\rShe is the one who created the Undine Strike and Soporific Whisper\rtechniques.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50084	8C8CEF	Liu Chienying Trophy	^FFCB4ALio Gianni is one of the Four Great Commanders. In the Battle\rof Two Cities, the Winged Elves dispatched all of their elite\rtroops, but Lio Gianni's brilliant strategies pushed them back\rwhile optimizing the city's defenses.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50085	8C8CEF	Fox Lady Trophy	^FFCB4ATrue to their heritage as self-aware foxes, serpents, and other\rvermin, the Venomancers are subtle, relying on poisons or curses\rto bring down enemies. They can also control animals or transform\rinto foxes for an additional set of skills.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50086	8C8CEF	Bestial Trophy	^FFCB4AThe Untamed are descendants of the animals \rthat evolved sentience. With berserker rage \rand animal cunning, they still carry the \rbeast in their hearts.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50087	8C8CEF	Priest Trophy	^FFCB4AThe Winged Elves are the most beautiful people among their\rcontemporaries. Gifted with flight from a young age, they can\rbe seemingly aloof and reclusive. Yet, those who are familiar\rwith them, find Winged Elves to be staunch allies.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50088	8C8CEF	Archer Trophy	^FFCB4AArchers hail from an ancient and divine bloodline. \rTheir exquisite form and unique wings grant them \rthe ability to fly. As the guardian of Winged Elf, they \rare outstanding archers and brave warriors, good at \rusing ranged weapons like the bow.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50089	8C8CEF	Psychic Trophy	^FFCB4AThe Tideborn class no longer pursue mastery of the elements,\rbut now manipulate the essence and instincts of creatures.\rThey manifest their will through Soulforce to enhance them-selves\rand their allies while harming their enemies.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50090	8C8CEF	Assassin Trophy	^FFCB4AStriking from the shadows, a dagger in the back, and a silent\rretreat are trademarks of an Assassin. Assassins are not brute\rmelee fighters, but masters of finesse. They prefer to rely on\ragility rather than bulky armor.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50091	8C8CEF	Mystic Trophy 	^FFCB4AA Mystic affects others with their grace and tenderness. With\rthe ability to communicate with the spiritual beings of nature,\rthey summon them as weapons. Vines, thorns, and trees are just a\rfraction of their arsenal. A Mystic also possesses miraculous\rhealing power, providing full support to teammates during combat.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50092	8C8CEF	Seeker Trophy	^FFCB4AaSeekers train in both the martial and arcane arts, and use the\relement of metal to enhance their close-combat swordplay. Each\rSeeker bears a relic upon their forehead that can discern evil.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50093	8C8CEF	Stormbringer Trophy	^FFCB4AThe specialty of Stormbringer their its ability to move-and‚Äìcast. They use scythe as their weapon, \rkitting their enemies while casting controls spells on them, making them hard to be caught. \rWith their powerful battle capabilities and defensieve spells, the Stormbringer has extremely high \rsurvivability, they are the nightmare of melee fighters.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50094	8C8CEF	Duskblade Trophy	^FFCB4AThe specialty of Duskblade is their ability to gap-close from a distance. Unlike other melee fighters, \rthey can dash to their enemies, and defeat them with rapid skill chains. The Duskblade has \rhigh flexibility and a variety of control skills, making them the most efficient killers among the \rbattlefields.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50095	8C8CEF	Flame Emperor Locen Trophy	^FFCB4AThe bloodthirsty South Sovereign of Morai. To him, there is no\rbetter pleasure than killing and pillaging. Leaving fire and\rdestruction in his wake, Locen truly is a monster.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50096	8C8CEF	Ghost Wing Trophy	^FFCB4AThe proud Upper Sovereign of Morai. As the overlord in the sky,\rhe possesses the sharpest eyes amongst the Sovereigns. Looking\rdown upon the other five sovereigns, he is only loyal and devoted\rto Aurogon, and ruthless to all creatures who enter his airspace.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50097	8C8CEF	Dark Emperor Aohe Trophy	^FFCB4AThe cunning East Sovereign of Morai. He is a trickster who can\rtransform into different people. Shrewd and silent, he hides his\rown ambition when giving advice to Aurogon. He organizes a faction\rwith Yakku and Biran, conspiring on the sly.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50098	8C8CEF	Mistress of Night Trophy	^FFCB4AThe beautiful but capricious West Sovereign of Morai. Sometimes,\rshe is sweet and mild. Sometimes, she is quite cold-blooded. She\rhates men very much, but she obeys Aohe's every word.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50099	8C8CEF	Gorath, the Worldrender Trophy	^FFCB4AThe miserly North Sovereign of Morai. Biran is despised by\rAurogon because he is a greedy coward. Aohe drew Biran to his\rside, valuing his powerful strength. Biran will betray anyone\ras long as it's profitable to do so.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50100	8C8CEF	Serpent Emperor Chigo Trophy	^FFCB4AThe headstrong Central Sovereign of Morai. Deeply trusted by\rAurogon, Chigo draws up the final plan. He kills Glory, the Elder's\rson, and takes on his appearance. Then, he activates the Undying\rDial, attempting to rebuild the wraith land.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50101	8C8CEF	Painted Waterstrider Trophy	^FFCB4AThis one is the apprentice of Seclusive Painter Yolan. The ink which Yolan uses is made by her hands. She is now guarding the Isle of Painting with her master.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50102	8C8CEF	Painted Windchaser Trophy	^FFCB4AThis one is the apprentice of Seclusive Painter Yolan. He is the retainer of Yolan's pets. He is now guarding the Isle of Painting with his master.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50103	8C8CEF	Bamboo Flute Girl Trophy	^FFCB4AA flute-playing child, whom likes to learn from the Unfettered Lady.\rFortunately for her that flute is a wonderful instrument.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50104	8C8CEF	Blossom Succubus Trophy	^FFCB4AMushi was in pursuit of a young lady for love, but he failed to catch her heart. Out of frastration,\rhe enslaved the lady in his palace, torturing and humiliating her. Eventually, the\rlady was no more, for a fearsome Blossom Succubus was born.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50105	8C8CEF	Tyrant Prince Mushi Trophy	^FFCB4AIt is said that inside the Flowsilver Palace, the tyrant's secret vault is hidden somewhere. The\rvault contains the rarest rarities, but to get into the vault, one must deal with the deadly traps\rlies on their path. When Mush was defeated, he fleed to the palace, planning to use the buried\rtreasures to rebuild his reign. Flowsilver Palace\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50106	8C8CEF	Century Golden Toad Trophy	^FFCB4AWhen the Flowsilver Palace was built, the ancestors of Mu family heeled a geomancer's advice\rand placed hundreds of posion toads inside the vault. Although toads made good treasure\rguardians, the rich geomantic energy of the palace allowed one of the toads to gain intelligence,\ralong with greed. The greedy toad have devoured all the other toads during a hunred years just to hoard the treasures all to itself. The tyrant has proved its power and\rintelligence, and granted it infinte amount of treasures in exchange for its service of guarding\rthe vault.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50107	8C8CEF	High Sage Esher Trophy	^FFCB4AThe Second Celestial Ascension was built with the rarest gems among the world, hence the breathtaking luxury\rcan be seen when one step into the hall, which is why High Sage Esher, the most infamous treasure maniac, is\rin charge of the place now. Esher is eccentric and unreasonable, he likes to turn his victims into golden statues,\rand then cruelly humiliate them.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50108	8C8CEF	Mara Papman Trophy	^FFCB4AThe Sixth Celestial Ascension was a peaceful and tranquil place, but now the dwell of Mara Papman,\revil and obscene. The place is filled with mist that even sunlight could not penetrate.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50109	8C8CEF	Matreya the Corrupt Trophy	^FFCB4AThe Fourth Celestial Ascension is the dwell of Matreya. The place was meant to be tranquil and solemn, but now,\rit's filled with deadly poison mist along with the fiends who created it.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50110	8C8CEF	Bodhi of Grief Trophy	^FFCB4AThe Third Celestial Ascension is a heavenly garden painted with a mysterious blue atmosphere.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50111	8C8CEF	Marei Ciah Trophy	^FFCB4AThe magicked statues of the four lords stand besides the pillars of coiled dragon, awing those\rwho dare to step inside.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50112	8C8CEF	Zen Witch Trophy	^FFCB4AThe dwellers of the Fifth Celestial Ascension were saints, they had no greed and no intrigue or other harmful\rthoughts. However, their blood has shed the place scarlet when the Serpent Witch came and executed her\rbloody massacre. \r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50113	8C8CEF	Gelid Dragon Trophy	^FFCB4AThe Gelid Dragon is most fearsome vanguard among its kin, yet he shared no common nature with them\r‚Äî‚Äî instead of attacking from above, he prefers to charge on the ground, like a cavalry.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50114	8C8CEF	Conflagration Dragon Trophy	^FFCB4AThe most fierce warrior of the Conflagration family. Do not underestimate her tiny body, for her\rsearing flame will vaporize those who dare to laugh at her.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50115	8C8CEF	Flame Dragon Overseer Trophy	^FFCB4AThe top-commander of the Flame Dragon Abyss. He never compromised on anything and he sees only\rpower as the mean to measure everything‚Äî‚Äîhe would even ally an enemy if he finds them strong enough.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50116	8C8CEF	Frost Queen Trophy	^FFCB4AShe was a powerful sorceress of the north, until she met the dragons of Frost family. She made\ra pact with them and became even something that is beyond powerful, even dragons started\rto fear of her. She is the Frost Queen.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50117	8C8CEF	Lord of Paradise Trophy	^FFCB4AHumans are always fighting; against their fate, against those who oppose them, and even\ragainst their own kin. Most of them will become powerful, but they will eventually fall under their\rown weight. Only those who can overcome themselves will triumph in the end. The Mirage Ocean\rLord would give everyone a chance to defeat themselves, and only with success may they challenge the final\rOverlord.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50118	8C8CEF	Seclusive Painter Yolan Trophy	^FFCB4AYolan lived a long life, she was an apprentice of the Elder Celestial of Painting, and she certainly\rtook her time with her painting skill. She treasures her pen, Celestta, which is given by her\rmaster, and she occasionly use it to turn someone into little animals for fun. To this date,\rYolan is still in pursuit of painting a perfect painting while guarding the Uncharted Paradise.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50119	8C8CEF	Flame Empress Astrid Trophy	^FFCB4AAstrid is short, but fiery-tempered.\rAs the Dragonborne, she can withstand fire and tame dragons.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50120	8C8CEF	Light Empress Althea Trophy 	^FFCB4AThe noble queen of the Light Nation. A strong but benevolent\rruler, she is greatly adored by all her people and soldiers.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50121	8C8CEF	Dark Empress Lorelei Trophy	^FFCB4AThough gentle in appearance, Lorelei, queen of the Twilight\rEmpire, is a true veteran of the seas. She is the captain of\rthe Dragonlord, an impressive warship. Sharp and aloof, she can\rcome across as intimidating even to her own soldiers.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50122	8C8CEF	Frost Empress Kestra Trophy	^FFCB4AThe empress of the Frost Nation, she eternally craves absolute\rpower. When she blows her horn, hundreds of thousands of\rbarbarians will respond with a roar.\r\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50123	8C8CEF	Lame Drinker Weist Trophy	^FFCB4AThere is this strange monk in the priam world, who, easts meat that he shouldn't be eating, and\rdrink meads that he should be avoiding. On top of that, he is not capable of handlling drinking, rthat he could literally get drunk after a mere bottle of drink. Nevertheless, this weirdo would\rbecome righteous when drunk, helping people to with their works and smashing bandits left\rand right. The folks who witnessed his deeds have even built a temple for him. What they\rdidn't know is that the weirdo they built the temple for is an actual Celestial ‚Äî‚Äî the Celestial\rof Drinking. It is said that there are only two types of folks who could pass his trial: the best drinker, and the naughtiest child.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50124	8C8CEF	Unfettered Lady Trophy	^FFCB4AOut of the boredom of serving as a dancer in feasts, the Unfettered Lady has left the heaven and gone\rto seek the way to weave melodies. Since then, she cares and only cares about music, and she is extremely\renthusiastic about competing her melodies with other master musicians. If you are up to her trial, make sure\ryou are skilled enough, only then could you earn her respect.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50125	8C8CEF	Dark Commander Trophy	^FFCB4AThis has become an everlasting and timeless chess match, and Red would not stop challenging\rBlack unless he wins. Some force from the outside world needs to be drawn in to put an end\rto Red's obsessiveness. \r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50126	8C8CEF	Wordless Scholar Trophy	^FFCB4ANo one could detail the origin of the Wordless Scholar, all they found was a line of text: ‚ÄúIn the chaotic past,\rwhere no good is left in the world. A four-eyed, dual-winged saint ventures out of the mountain. He educated\rkings with discipline, and rectified folks with laws. Eventually, the light of justice has once again shed upon the\rtroubled land.‚Äù The saint was later known as the Wordless Scholar, an otherworldly being who does not belong\rto our world. He detest fighting with brute force, favoring games of mind and literatures. To pass\rhis trial, you must possess enough knowledge and wisdom, or you will be punished, horribly.\r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
50127	8C8CEF	Pathkeeper Bajan Trophy	^FFCB4ALong before the mortal world clamity, there was a fearsome commander, Bajan. He led a hundred warriors and expelled the evil forces from the world. Though the world was always in chaos before and after his death, his merit was remembered by the peaceful people. When the gods set up the challenges, they selected Bajan to be the first guardian. \r^00FFFFRight-click to use. Can only be used in the Homestead.	99	16403	0
